   <conbody>
      <p platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/p ">Redundant systems always have parallel communication
cables. The parallel communication cables are optional in dual systems
but must be used if the system has a couple switch.</p>
      <p platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/p ">The parallel communication is redundant and
sends the same signals in both cables. The signals are sent between
the parallel operation board <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(A024)</b> and the controller board <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(A070)</b> in both units.</p>
      <p platform="SDC" class="- topic/p ">Redundant systems always have a parallel communication
cable. The signal is sent between the external connection boards <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(A025)</b> in both units.</p>
